# Leacme.Always Up

**Leacme Always Up** is a cross-platform application that is currently targeted for mobile devices. It is build using the [Godot Engine](https://github.com/godotengine/godot).

This application features the ability to always point in the direction of opposite your device's gravity sensor potentially assisting in finding orientation.

![][image_screenshot]
![index](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6654513/71701622-e12ed880-2d87-11ea-9dd7-6e5d6d5fe740.png)

## Application Compiling

The application can be compiled into the platform-specific executable with the Godot Engine via the following [instructions](https://docs.godotengine.org/en/latest/getting_started/workflow/export/index.html). Make sure to run `nuget restore` to fetch dependencies specified in the .csproj file prior to building with Godot.

## Application Usage

Launch the app and the arrow should point up - opposite to the gravitation field estimated by your device.
